Spanish Stocks: Bankinter, Santander, Gamesa, Repsol Shares Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-04-07T16:34:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/spanish-stocks-bankinter-santander-bbva-repsol-shares-move.html
Spain ’s IBEX 35 index advanced 4
points, or less than 0.1 percent, to 10,849.1 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in  Madrid . The Madrid Stock Exchange General Index rose
0.1 percent today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.  Bankinter SA (BKT)   rose 4.3 percent to 5.26 euros,
extending yesterday’s increase. Banks led gains today after
Spain sold 4.13 billion euros ($5.9 billion) of three-year bonds
and its borrowing costs fell as  Portugal  said it would seek a
European Union bailout.  Banco Santander SA (SAN)   climbed 1.7 percent to 8.56
euros.  Banco Popular Espanol SA (POP)   advanced 1.5 percent to
4.34 euros.  Gamesa Corporacion Tecnologica SA (GAM SM) fell 4.5 percent
to 7.10 euros, the most in almost six months. UBS AG cut Spain’s
largest wind-turbine maker to “sell” from “neutral,” citing
pricing pressures and more competition from Chinese producers.  Repsol YPF SA (REP)   lost 1.6 percent to 24.39 euros,
erasing yesterday’s gain. A union protest at Argentina’s Refinor
SA, a refinery that belongs to YPF SA and Petroleo Brasileiro
SA, cut natural gas imports from  Bolivia , threatening to reduce
supplies to industrial users, newspaper El Cronista said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  